20/04/2005
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Local police said Tuesday (19 April) that they have detained six Chechens, suspected of being Islamic terrorists.
The men, who were staying in Turkey illegally, were allegedly trying to collect information on bomb design and production.
A number of electronic devices, two laptops, CDs and a notebook that included information about bomb design were seized.
Also Tuesday, Turkey's Defence Ministry announced a $189m deal with two Israeli firms -- Israel Aircraft Industries and Elbit Systems -- for the supply of unmanned aerial vehicles and ground stations.
The two companies beat out French and US firms competing for the contract.
(NTV - 20/04/05;
NTV, TurkishPress.com, Turks.US - 19/04/05)
